 464 7129  If you are visiting from out of town  driving directions are available from the VMI Visitors  Information page  Parking in front of Preston Library is limited  Visitors are welcome to park wherever space is available  There is no charge for parking on post  Please note  Letcher Avenue is CLOSED to traffic during the academic year at the following times  0700 0730 Monday 0610 0620 Tuesday 0700 0715 Wednesday Saturday 12 1210 Daily 1800 1815 Daily 1900 1915 Daily 1630 1730 Friday 1030 1130 Saturday  Home Football Contests  Please plan your visit accordingly  Circulation policy Preston Library extends borrowing privileges to Rockbridge County residents  as well as faculty and students at Washington   Lee University  Southern Virginia University  and other Virginia colleges  Visit the circulation desk to fill out a brief registration form  Computer and Internet Access Preston Library provides public access to the internet via 32 network computers in addition to the wireless network  All study carrels are equipped with power outlets and ethernet connections  WiFi is available throughout the library  with the preferred network for visitors  patrons who don t have a VMI network username and password  Preston Public  Read more about the library s wireless networks here  Photocopies Black and white photocopies can be made at the circulation desk and cost 10  per page plus tax as required by the state  Dedicated spaces and art in Preston Library Here is a list of the dedicated study carrels  Here is a listed of named dedicated areas in the library  Information about portraits located in Preston Library can be found here Please call  540  464 7129 with questions about visiting Preston Library  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military 